# Linting

## Invoke via pre-commit

- When a repo has `pre-commit` configured, run linters/validators via
  `pre-commit run <hook-id> --all-files`, not the tool binary directly — the binary
  may not be on `PATH` outside the pre-commit virtualenv.
- To verify a change set, prefer a single `pre-commit run --all-files` (or scoped to
  touched files) over hand-assembling equivalent checks.
- If `pre-commit` (or any check tool) is a project-managed dependency, resolve how to
  invoke it via `my-mise-en-place` rather than assuming it's on bare `PATH` — don't
  hardcode a runner prefix here.

## Hooks are the contract

- When a hook fails, fix the source so it conforms. Do not skip the hook, add inline
  silencers (`# noqa`, `# fmt: skip`), or extend `exclude:` patterns to dodge it.
- The only legitimate excludes are structural incompatibilities (vendored files,
  binary-like blobs). Silencing a hook otherwise needs explicit user approval.
